<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12
        ENGINES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Vehicle Speed Signal
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Vehicle Speed Signal</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>VSS Adjustment: Turn sensor in until it bottoms out, then back off one full turn.</para>
            <para>Construct test leads using terminals 1680205C1, short length of 16 gauge wire and alligator clips.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>A jack must never be used alone to support vehicle. The jack may lower and serious injury
                        could result. Always support vehicle with floor jacks. Always block wheels to prevent vehicle
                        from moving.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>EXTREME CAUTION should be used to prevent personal injury resulting from contact with rotating
                        vehicle wheels when connecting test leads.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (531)</title>
            <table id="t0823708" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor (531)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.27in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inspect VSS for damage and proper adjustment before performing this test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect engine harness connector (531) from VSS and use test leads to measure
                                    resistance between terminal A and B of the sensor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>600 to 800 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance to ground at both terminals (A and B) of the sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, A and B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS sensor output test: This test checks for proper AC voltage output signal from
                                    VSS sensor. Improper sensor adjustment will cause low, erratic or no output.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid personal contact with
                                    rotating vehicle wheels during test. Connect meter leads to sensor test leads.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Run engine at idle speed with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across
                                    the two sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>2.0 volts AC.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The vehicle speed sensor checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If sensor was properly adjusted, replace the sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor To ECM Circuits</title>
            <para>This procedure tests the International speed sensor circuits between connectors (531) and (1014).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (1014) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0823709" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor To ECM Circuits</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.90in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.67in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.81in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.44in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (531) from VSS and (1014) from the ECM. At conn. (531) measure
                                    resistance to gnd. at both terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(531) both term's to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100 K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit (97AK or 97AJ), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At (531) measure resistance between terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(531), between term's.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short circuit between circuits 97AJ and 97AK, between connectors (531) and
                                    (1014), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (1014) use test lead to jumper terminal 33 to ground. At conn. (531)
                                    measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AK.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(531), 97AK to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AK, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (1014) use test lead to jumper terminal 32 to ground. At conn. (531)
                                    measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AJ.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(531), 97AJ to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Vehicle speed circuits and VSS check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AJ, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
